$ Powershell module console: set-consolePaletteColor

Set the color of an entry of the console color palette (as ordered in the *properties dialog* of
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/conhost_exe[`conhost.exe`]).

The function → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/console/get-paletteIndexOfConsoleColor[`get-paletteIndexOfConsoleColor`] turns
an entry of the → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/ConsoleColor[`System.ConsoleColor`] enum into
the index number of this (dialog-) palette.

The value of the first parameter must be between 0 and 15.

code {
$paletteIndex =   4
$r            = 197
$g            =  15
$b            =  31

set-consolePaletteColor $paletteIndex  $r $g  $b
code }

sa:
  This function is found in the PowerShell module → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/console[console].
